solution:
Begin by noticing that $256=16^2$.

We can then repeatedly apply a difference of squares factorization: \begin{align*}
x^8-256&=(x^4+16)(x^4-16)
&=(x^4+16)(x^2+4)(x^2-4)
&=\boxed{(x^4+16)(x^2+4)(x+2)(x-2)}
\end{align*}

Final Answer: (x^4+16)(x^2+4)(x+2)(x-2)

