$$

\left|\frac{f(t)-f(x)}{t-x}\right| \leq|t-x| \text {, hence } \lim _{t \rightarrow x}\left|\frac{f(t)-f(x)}{t-x}\right|=0 \text {, }

$$

so $f$ is differentiable in $\mathbb{R}$ and $f^{\prime}=0$. This implies that $f$ is constant, as seen in class.

\end{proof}

