:$x \mathrel \RR y \land y \mathrel \RR x \implies x \mathrel \RR x$\nAs $\RR$ is [[Definition:Serial Relation|serial]]:
:$\forall x \in S: \exists y \in S: x \mathrel \RR y$\nLet $x \in S$.\nThen
{{begin-eqn}}
{{eqn | lo= \exists y \in S:
| l = \tuple {x, y}
| o = \in
| r = \RR
| c = as $\RR$ is [[Definition:Serial Relation|serial]]
}}\n{{eqn | ll= \leadsto
| l = \tuple {y, x}
| o = \in
| r = \RR
| c = as $\RR$ is [[Definition:Symmetric Relation|symmetric]]
}}\n{{eqn | ll= \leadsto
| l = \tuple {x, x}
| o = \in
| r = \RR
| c = as $\RR$ is [[Definition:Transitive Relation|transitive]]
