\begin{proof}

Let $\phi$ be an automorphism of $G$. Let $P$ be a normal sylow p-subgroup. $\phi(P)$ is also a sylow-p subgroup. But since $P$ is normal, it is unique. Hence $\phi(P)=P$.

\end{proof}

