We substitute this value for $k$ into one of the equations to solve for $j$: \begin{align*}
2\left(\frac{-1}{2}\right)-j&=3 \quad \Rightarrow
j &= -4.

\end{align*}So the solution is $\boxed{(-4,-\frac{1}{2})}$.

